HEADWORD: Melilot
<hw>Mel"i*lot</hw> <pr>(-l⟦ocr⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>m⟦eacute⟧lilot</ets>, L. <ets>melilotus</ets>, fr. Gr. <?/, <?/, a
kind of clover containing honey; <grk>me`li</grk> honey + <?/
lotus.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Any species of
<gen>Melilotus</gen>, a genus of leguminous herbs having a vanillalike
odor; sweet clover; hart's clover. The blue melilot (<spn>Melilotus
caerulea</spn>) is used in Switzerland to give color and flavor to
sapsago cheese.</def>⟦br⟧
